ignatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"8ed212ad9256138bf2497e2c48d1e98d8a6d0868af629f74581186e3785822e4","event_uuid":"423c718f-2275-4401-9c52-0563cadcf80e","position":{"commit_sha":"202f0bf3877f9b5a1d1627d6a12d5031b6f8eebf","position":"1784685041980840001-423c718f-2275-4401-9c52-0563cadcf80e"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"f24d98b3d2da6803d849448c17b4c177a8bf087ada832ad071c3dc65ee40eb7d","event_uuid":"3a21020b-04af-46eb-9a2a-450553272083","position":{"commit_sha":"202f0bf3877f9b5a1d1627d6a12d5031b6f8eebf","position":"1784685042281956001-3a21020b-04af-46eb-9a2a-450553272083"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"c1c4660d061f4589767fe6db099236a8b470cb46be0549c227f931f07769cbd1","event_uuid":"842c0aa1-5dec-480b-aa46-01c761f0784a","position":{"commit_sha":"512faf2a4f5717b1685634cd6e8afecd620fd0eb","position":"1784685493161405386-842c0aa1-5dec-480b-aa46-01c761f0784a"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-217_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"007b200a-5427-4a88-a88c-815e2a8f9d31","comments":[],"created_at":1784581488591994001,"creation_channel":"import","deps":[],"description":"## Finding\n\nCanonical contributor guidance hardcodes a specific maintainer/bot DCO identity even though project contribution policy requires contributors to sign with their own real configured identity.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `AGENTS.md:124-169` documents the Gerrit workflow and currently prescribes `Signed-off-by: Joe Oakhart <joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com>`.\n- `.agents/rules/rebar.md:28-34` repeats the same personal bot identity.\n- `CONTRIBUTING.md:198-214` requires a real contributor name and email for DCO sign-off.\n\n## Remediation\n\nMake the canonical guidance identity-neutral: contributors and agents use the real name and email configured for the actor performing the commit (`git config user.name` / `git config user.email`). Retain Joe Oakhart's bot identity only in narrowly scoped automation guidance for a workflow that actually runs as that bot.\n\nCascade flag: documentation-only contract change; verify all imported/copied agent guidance (`AGENTS.md`, `.agents/rules/*.md`, and any other contributor-facing guidance under `docs/`) so contradictory instructions do not remain. Automation-owned paths (`infra/`, `.github/workflows/`, `tests/fixtures/`) and experiment corpora (`docs/experiments/`) legitimately reference the bot identity and are explicitly out of scope for the sweep and for the consistency check below.\n\nAdd a deterministic consistency check: a `make lint`-integrated grep step (e.g. a target in the `Makefile`, or a script under `scripts/` invoked from `make lint`) that runs\n`git grep -nE 'joeoakhart\\+bot@navapbc\\.com|Signed-off-by: Joe Oakhart' -- AGENTS.md '.agents/rules/*.md' CONTRIBUTING.md ':(glob)docs/**/*.md' ':(exclude)docs/experiments/**'`\n(the `:(glob)` pathspec magic makes `**` recurse into subdirectories under `docs/`; the `:(exclude)` pathspec drops `docs/experiments/` from the scan) and fails the build if it finds any match. `infra/`, `.github/workflows/`, and `tests/` are excluded by construction because they are not passed as pathspecs. Document, next to the check, which file owns it and that `infra/`/`.github/workflows/`/`tests/`/`docs/experiments/` are the intentional exclusions.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `AGENTS.md` tells contributors and agents to verify `git config user.name` and `git config user.email` and to sign off with that configured real identity. Verify: `grep -q 'git config user.name' AGENTS.md && grep -q 'git config user.email' AGENTS.md`.\n- [ ] `.agents/rules/rebar.md` and any derived guidance no longer instruct every actor to use Joe Oakhart's bot identity. Verify: `! git grep -nE 'joeoakhart\\+bot@navapbc\\.com|Signed-off-by: Joe Oakhart' -- '.agents/rules/*.md' AGENTS.md`.\n- [ ] Any retained Joe-specific identity is explicitly scoped to the automation that owns it (e.g. `infra/`, `.github/workflows/`, `CLAUDE.local.md`) and is not presented as general contributor guidance. Verify: `git grep -nE 'joeoakhart\\+bot@navapbc\\.com|Signed-off-by: Joe Oakhart'` returns matches ONLY under `infra/`, `.github/workflows/`, `tests/`, or `docs/experiments/`; any match outside those prefixes fails the check.\n- [ ] `CONTRIBUTING.md`, canonical agent guidance, and generated/imported guidance describe one consistent DCO contract, defined concretely as: all three name \"the committer's own configured git identity (`git config user.name`/`user.email`)\" as the sign-off source, and none of them names a specific third party (Joe Oakhart or otherwise) as the required sign-off for general contributions. Verify: `for f in CONTRIBUTING.md AGENTS.md .agents/rules/rebar.md; do grep -q \"configured git identity\" \"$f\" || exit 1; done` exits 0 (each file must contain the phrase, or the loop exits non-zero on the first miss), AND `git grep -l 'Signed-off-by: Joe Oakhart' -- CONTRIBUTING.md AGENTS.md '.agents/rules/*.md'` returns no results.\n- [ ] A deterministic consistency check exists and fails the build on a reintroduced hardcoded personal sign-off: implemented as a `make lint`-integrated grep step (script or Makefile target) running `git grep -nE 'joeoakhart\\+bot@navapbc\\.com|Signed-off-by: Joe Oakhart' -- AGENTS.md '.agents/rules/*.md' CONTRIBUTING.md ':(glob)docs/**/*.md' ':(exclude)docs/experiments/**'` (the `:(glob)` magic recurses into `docs/adr/`, `docs/design/`, `docs/migrations/`, `docs/calibration/`, etc.; `:(exclude)` drops `docs/experiments/`; `infra/`, `.github/workflows/`, `tests/` are excluded by not being passed as pathspecs) and fails the build (non-zero exit) if `git grep` finds any match. Verify: the new check's script/target exists, running it against the post-change guidance files exits 0, and running it against a scratch copy with the hardcoded string reinjected exits non-zero.\n\n\n\n","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"AGENTS.md","reason":"Canonical DCO and Gerrit instructions"},{"path":".agents/rules/rebar.md","reason":"Derived agent sign-off instructions"},{"path":"CONTRIBUTING.md","reason":"Authoritative contributor DCO policy"},{"path":"tests","reason":"Documentation consistency coverage"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","6eca-183e-1cd2-4fb9"]],"parent_id":"6eca-183e-1cd2-4fb9","parent_status_uuid":"423c718f-2275-4401-9c52-0563cadcf80e","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":1,"reverts":[],"source_author":"ChatGPT","source_created_at":1784525662047870745,"source_env":"0af3c941-9543-4bc4-a360-bc56759da47a","source_id":"11d9-f190-f2f6-45f3","status":"in_progress","tags":["janitor","documentation","dco"],"ticket_id":"35d2-8cd6-161c-4e7f","ticket_type":"story","title":"Make contributor sign-off guidance identity-neutral","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["7d4b4026-1450-431c-b817-36b5a00939a7","1